line_1: I sat and ey'd the spewing reek,
I sat and ey'd the spewing reek,
I sat and ey'd the spewing reek,
line_2: And heard the restless rattons squeak

line_1: Along the Sands the panting Pieces reek,
line_2: And ev'n in Death a Shelter seem to seek.
Sages their solemn een may steek,
But tell me Whisky's name in Greek,
